    subHeader: "",
    contentHeader: 'SANREMO FESTIVAL 2023 BEST LOOKS',
    content: "<p class='first'>The 73rd edition of the Sanremo Festival has just ended, and it left us with some very memorable moments, but most of all with some pretty iconic fashion looks.</p><p>The Sanremo Festival was born in 1951 as a national song contest that lasts one week and plays out once a year in February. Over time, the contest has evolved from just a music environment to a broader range of creative industry representatives, such as actors, comedians, journalists, and influencers. It is a very entertaining annual date to which Italians look forward at each start of the year.  Being one of the highlights of Italian television, Sanremo is one of the top opportunities for emerging artists to enhance their popularity and for fashion designers to showcase their latest works.</p>Without further ado let's talk fashion. </p><p>Here are the Most Fashionable Moments of the 2023 Sanremo Festival Edition. </p><h3>1)Chiara Ferragni</h3><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/chiara-1.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/chiara-2.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px] py-2 text-center break-words col-span-2'>Image credit: Instagram - @chiaraferragni</p></div><p>The first one on our list has to be <b>Chiara Ferragni</b>, Italy’s very own Kylie Jenner (in terms of influencer popularity, not looks of course).  Chiara is a blogger, businesswoman, fashion designer, and model, who gained her popularity through her website “The Blonde Salad”.</p><p>On the opening night of the festival, she wanted to send a very strong message to women against hate, violence, and sexism. The first one is called “The Manifesto Dress”, designed by Dior, with a stole reciting “Think of yourself as free”. The message is directed at women who are tired of having to fit in with society-imposed roles. The second one, also custom-made by Dior, was named “The Shameless dress”, giving the illusion of nudity, and standing against the objectification of women's bodies. </p><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/chiara-3.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/chiara-4.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px] py-2 text-center break-words col-span-2'>Image credit: Instagram - @chiaraferragni</p></div><p>Chiara also wore a black Schiaparelli dress with a womb-shaped golden necklace representing reproductive rights. Finally, in our last selected look, “The Cage Dress”, designed once again by Dior, alludes to women who want to break free from their patriarchy-assigned roles. She is intentionally depicted with her daughter who represents the fact that this hope that lies in the next generation of women. </p><h3>2)	Elodie </h3><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/elodie-1.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/elodie-2.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: Instagram - @maisonvalentino</p><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: https://www.vogue.it/</p></div><p><b>Elodie</b> is an Italian singer, actress, and model. She also appeared in the Vogue Italia 2023 February edition. Her best two looks for the Sanremo 2023 Festival included a Valentino birdie look, seen in Pierpaolo Piccioli’s latest fashion show. For the closing night, she wore a very trending Versace gothic-chic look with a single-laced glove sleeve. </p><h3>3)Mara Sattei</h3><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/mara-1.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/mara-2.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: https://www.vanityfair.it/</p><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: Instagram - @mara.sattei</p></div><p><b>Mara Sattei</b> is an Italian singer-songwriter. One of her best looks was designed by Giorgio Armani Privé. The long purple, blue, green – but mostly black – nuanced dress is embellished by Chopard Maison jewels. </p><h3>4)Tananai</h3><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/tananai-1.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/tananai-2.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: Instagram - @amicamagazine </p><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: https://www.vogue.it/</p></div><p><b>Tananai</b> is an Italian singer and songwriter. He chose Maison Gucci to represent his persona for the 73rd edition of Sanremo. The top 2 looks are from the third and fourth nights of the festival.</p><p>The first look consists of a regular suit and a double-breasted jacket with jeweled buttons, adorned with a silk pocket handkerchief, and a pair of soft trousers with turn-ups, all cut from blue wool fabric with contrasting thin red pattern.</p><p>The second look is a grey suit with Seventies lines, marked shoulders, and flared trousers. </p><h3>5)Francesca Fagnani</h3><div class='grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-2 '><div class='w-[200px]  m-auto sm:w-[400px]  sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/fagnani-1.jpg' class='object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><div class='w-[200px] m-auto  sm:w-[400px] sm:h-[500px]'><img src='/images/fagnani-2.jpg' class=' object-cover h-full w-full' /></div><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: Instagram - @amica magazine </p><p class='text-[13px]  text-center break-words '>Image credit: https://www.elle.com/it/moda//</p></div><p>Francesca Fagnani is an Italian journalist and TV presenter. For the first night of the festival, she wore a Giorgio Armani Privé long and elegant dress. The nude tulle dress engages in a well-thought transparency scheme and is embellished by Pasquale Bruni’s jewels. </p>",
