    mainHeader: "London Fashion Week - Beauty Trends",
    subHeader: "",
    contentHeader: "London Fashion Week - Beauty Trends",
    content:
      "<p class='first'>This season's London Fashion Week has overcome many challenges as the city commemorates Queen Elizabeth II's life and legacy. As 2022 comes to a close, we're preparing for Spring/Summer 2023 with the hottest makeup and beauty trends.</p><p>This season was full of breathtaking makeup touches that wowed fashion enthusiasts both on and off the catwalks. London Fashion Week SS23 did not disappoint, from a pop of colours to bright shades, berry lips, and sparkling glitter! </p><p>Is it time to revamp and boost your makeup routine? Keep an eye on Brits' beauty inspirations! Read on to discover this season's fascinating makeup trends from London.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Brow Lamination</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'>Photo: Alex Soroka - Courtesy of Isamaya</p></div><p>The brow lamination trend has already taken off and will continue to snowball in Spring/Summer 2023, but with a twist! The classic approach to brows at Poster Girl has been reimagined in favor of accentuated, razor-cut brows by makeup artist Isamaya Ffrench, while fluffy, brushed-up brows have been very much in vogue recently. So how far you take the brow shape next season is up to you!</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Embellished Disco Eyes</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-2.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'> Photographed by Acielle/StyleDuMonde</p></div><p>Regarding SS23 beauty trends, embellished eyes are here to stay. Halpern and Mark Fast used mixed bright highlighter colours with geometric shapes and jewels to enhance the eye look at Paul and Joe. Also, keep the skin fresh and radiant with a skin tint and a 'your lips but better' subtle shine to give the style a new spring/summer touch.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Berry Lips</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-3.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'>Nick England - BFC - Getty Images</p></div><p>Cherry red lips were reserved for cooler winter days, but they’re more likely to become a year-round love affair this time. During this fashion week, the strong lip style was matched with brushed-up, fluffy brows and barely eye makeup that let the lips do the talking, ranging from nearly black to raspberry colours.</p><p><strong>A small tip:</strong> To keep your lipstick in place all day, use a lip pencil around the borders of your mouth, or dab the edges with your finger for an undone look.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Laminated Skin</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-4.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'> Photo by Jacqueline Kilikita</p></div><p>Highlighters are about more than just brightened cheekbones or powdered, glittering finishes in Spring/Summer 2023. It's about making a 'hyper-moisturized' and 'laminated' base, as described by Terry Barber, MAC's director of makeup artistry. </p><p>Everyone can benefit from glossy, laminated skin; even acne-prone and uneven skin. It's only a matter of adapting your skin to it. Before applying makeup, avoid using an oily base and use a lightweight gel moisturizer instead.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Bleached Brows</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-5.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'>Photographed by Acielle/StyleDuMonde</p></div><p>If you've been following fashion runways, you'll notice that brow trends change with each season. And this Spring/Summer 2023 is all about bare brows!</p><p>Want to try the look without bleaching your brows? Use the creamiest concealer in a slightly lighter shade, then use a spoolie to coat them once or twice. It will give you an idea of how your face would look if you follow that route.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>Colour Flash</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-6.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'>Victor Virgile - Getty Images</p></div><p>A full-eye look full of colours can be too much for many, but that’s not a problem because a quick swipe of pastel shadow or liner is a gorgeous way to play with colour this season.</p><p>You can go for the inner or outer corners of the eye is a striking beauty statement easily done and can 100% work for day or evening. Purple shades were highly noticed on the London catwalks, but blue or green shades were noticed on various street style stars.</p><h3 class='sub-head'>A Pop of Glitter</h3><div><img src='/images/londonFashion-7.jpg' class='block m-auto h-[400px] object-cover'/><p class='text-sm text-center py-2'>Nick England- BFC - Getty Images</p></div><p>We've seen glitter used in make-up before, but it appears that the bursts of glitter during New York Fashion Week leaped across the pond this season, with numerous designers prepping their models for the catwalk in various shades of shine. Of course, there is no limit to how much glitter you'll use this season, so the more, the merrier!</p>",
