    subHeader: "",
    contentHeader: "Demand for Kanye West's Yeezy Sneakers Surges Instead of Slumps, According to CEO",
    content: "<p class='first'>Adidas dropped Kanye West's Yeezy brand after his antisemitic comments last year, but the controversy seems to have driven demand for the sneakers. The Yeezy sneakers are now one of the top three sellers on Impossible Kicks, a large online reseller of high-end sneakers and clothing. &quot;Demand for Yeezys has surged 30% since last October-November,&quot; said John Mocadlo, CEO of Impossible Kicks.</p><img src='/images/kanye-1.jpg' alt='kanye' class='block m-auto'/> <p class='text-[12px] text-center py-1 figcaption'>Image from unsplash.com</p><p>Yeezy sneakers are among the most popular brands on the platform after Jordans and other Nike footwear, including Dunk and Air Max shoes. Impossible Kicks sells around 30,000 sneakers in total every month, with approximately 6,000 to 7,000 of those being Yeezys.</p><p>The Yeezy 350 with black and white in the shoe's color pattern is among the most sought-after at resale, priced 20% to 40% above the shoe's retail value, according to Mocadlo. The resale price for those two options ranges from $350 to $400. The increased sales of Yeezy's at resale wouldn't benefit West because the secondary market represents items that were already purchased.</p><img src='/images/yeezy.jpg' alt='kanye' class='block m-auto'/> <p class='text-[12px] text-center py-1 figcaption'>Image from <a href='https://news.adidas.com/'>https://news.adidas.com/</a></p><p>Mocadlo stated that many customers hoping to score Yeezy sneakers view them as collector's items, hoping to see a further increase in value. While others simply like their style and comfort and want to add them to their wardrobe. He added that many customers are unaware of the controversy tied to the brand's designer. &quot;I'm very surprised by that,&quot; he said.</p><p>Adidas, which had been working with West since 2013 to produce and market his Yeezy brand, wasn't the only company to cut ties with him. The fallout extended to Gap, Footlocker, TJ Maxx, and Balenciaga, all of which stopped selling Yeezy merchandise.</p><p>Earlier this month, Adidas said it expects to lose $1.3 billion in revenue this year after ending its nine-year partnership with West, leaving the company stuck with a lot of unsold Yeezy-branded merchandise. The company said it would try to repurpose some of it without the Yeezy branding.</p><p>Impossible Kicks has about $2 million in Yeezy sneaker inventory currently, approximately 10,000 pairs. &quot;It is getting a little bit difficult to get more because the inventory is starting to dry up after the controversy,&quot; said Mocadlo.</p><img src='/images/kanye-2.jpg' alt='kanye' class='block m-auto'/> <p class='text-[12px] text-center py-1 figcaption'>Image from <a href='https://runthetrap.com/'>https://runthetrap.com/</a></p><p>Prices for Yeezy sneakers are now climbing due to tighter supply, according to StockX, a leading sneaker resale platform. &quot;Since the start of the year, the average price of Yeezy sneakers has increased, but sales overall have decreased on StockX,&quot; said Drew Haines, director of sneakers and collectibles at StockX. &quot;This is in line with the principles of supply and demand and consistent with what we'd expect to happen when no new supply is in the market.&quot; StockX declined to comment specifically on demand for Yeezy sneakers on its platform.</p>",
    month: "MAR 2023 EDITION",
    img: "/images/yeezy.jpg",
    author: "Omotoyosi Osikoya",
    topics: ["FASHION & BEAUTY", "CELEBRITY FASHION"],
    theme: "",
    date: "March 01, 2023",
    template: 3,
